As per the [2020 United States Census](/2020_United_States_census), the city of Pensacola recorded a population of 54,312 individuals, comprising 24,748 households and 13,470 families. [57] The [population density](/Population_density) was calculated at 2,395.7 inhabitants per square mile (925.0/km 2 ). The city contained 27,892 housing units, with an average density of 1,230.3 per square mile (475.0/km 2 ). The racial composition of the city was reported as 66.16% [White](/White_(U.S._census)), 22.41% [African American](/African_American_(U.S._Census)), 0.43% [Native American](/Native_American_(U.S._Census)), 2.47% [Asian](/Asian_(U.S._Census)), 0.09% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)), 1.39% identifying with other races, and 7.05% identifying with two or more races. [Hispanic or Latino](/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans) individuals, regardless of race, constituted 5.23% of the population. [58]

#### 2010 census

According to the [2010 United States Census](/2010_United_States_census), Pensacola had a population of 51,923 residents, distributed across 23,592 households. The population density was 2,303.5 inhabitants per square mile (889.4/km 2 ). The city featured 26,848 housing units, with an average density of 1,191.1 per square mile (459.9/km 2 ). The racial makeup of the city was 66.34% [White](/White_(U.S._census)), 27.98% [African American](/African_American_(U.S._Census)), 0.56% [Native American](/Native_American_(U.S._Census)), 2.00% [Asian](/Asian_(U.S._Census)), 0.12% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)), 0.70% from other races, and 2.30% from two or more races. [Hispanic or Latino](/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans) individuals constituted 3.30% of the population.

#### 2000 census

The [2000 United States Census](/2000_United_States_census) recorded a population of 56,255 in Pensacola, residing in 24,524 households and 14,665 families. The population density was 2,478.7 inhabitants per square mile (957.0/km 2 ). There were 26,995 housing units, averaging a density of 1,189.4 per square mile (459.2/km 2 ). The racial composition was 64.91% [White](/White_(U.S._census)), 30.58% [African American](/African_American_(U.S._Census)), 0.52% [Native American](/Native_American_(U.S._Census)), 1.77% [Asian](/Asian_(U.S._Census)), 0.06% [Pacific Islander](/Pacific_Islander_(U.S._Census)), 0.54% from other races, and 1.61% from two or more races. [Hispanic or Latino](/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans) individuals represented 2.07% of the population.

Of the 24,524 households, 24.6% included children under the age of 18. Married couples accounted for 39.7% of households, while 16.7% were headed by a female householder with no husband present. Non-family households comprised 40.2% of the total. Individuals living alone made up 32.9% of households, with 11.7% consisting of individuals aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.27, and the average family size was 2.92.

The age distribution within the city showed 22.9% under 18, 8.9% between 18 and 24, 26.9% from 25 to 44, 24.0% from 45 to 64, and 17.2% aged 65 or older. The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females, there were 88.5 males, and for every 100 females aged 18 and over, there were 84.7 males.

The median income for a household in Pensacola was $34,779, and for a family, it was $42,868. Males reported a median income of $32,258, compared to $23,582 for females. The [per capita income](/Per_capita_income) for the city was $21,438. A significant 16.1% of the population and 12.7% of families were living below the [poverty line](/Poverty_threshold), with 26.2% of those below the poverty line being under 18 and 9.2% being 65 or older.

