[Five Flags Speedway](/Five_Flags_Speedway), a half-mile paved racetrack inaugurated in 1953, hosts the prestigious [Snowball Derby](/Snowball_Derby) stock car race annually in December since 1968. The track has also served as a venue for various racing series, including rounds of the NASCAR Grand National (now [NASCAR Cup Series](/NASCAR_Cup_Series)), [Superstar Racing Experience](/Superstar_Racing_Experience), [NASCAR Southeast Series](/NASCAR_Southeast_Series), [ARCA Racing Series](/ARCA_Racing_Series), [ARCA Menards Series East](/ARCA_Menards_Series_East), [ASA National Tour](/American_Speed_Association), [CARS Pro Cup Series](/CARS_Pro_Cup_Series), and the Southern Super Series.

