#### Mass transit

The local bus service is provided by [Escambia County Area Transit](/Escambia_County_Area_Transit) (ECAT). [91] ECAT operates both fixed-route bus services and paratransit services. The current ECAT system includes fixed-route bus service, a seasonal Pensacola Beach trolley, and a trolley service operating on the University of West Florida campus. [91] Bus schedules and real-time tracking are available via the moovit website and mobile application. [92] The app can be downloaded from the ECAT website, which also provides details on the service area and route listings. [93]

Pensacola also features a ferry service managed by the National Park Service, with stops connecting Downtown Pensacola, Pensacola Beach, and Fort Pickens.

#### Bus

The city is served by [Greyhound Bus](/Greyhound_Bus) and [Greyhound Lines](/Greyhound_Lines). [94]

#### Hospitals

Hospitals located in Pensacola include Ascension Sacred Heart Hospital, Baptist Hospital, Encompass Health Rehabilitation Hospital, HCA Florida West Hospital, and Select Specialty Hospital. [95]

